com.cloudera.labs.envelope.plan

Class EventTimeUpsertPlanner

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cloudera.labs.envelope.plan.EventTimeUpsertPlanner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Component, InstantiatesComponents, ProvidesAlias, Planner, RandomPlanner, ProvidesValidations

    public class EventTimeUpsertPlanner
extends Object
implements RandomPlanner, ProvidesAlias, ProvidesValidations, InstantiatesComponents
    A planner implementation for updating existing and inserting new (upsert). This maintains the most recent version of the values of a key, which is equivalent to Type I SCD modeling.

                                     List<Row> arrivingForKey,
                                     List<Row> existingForKey)
        Description copied from interface: RandomPlanner
        Plan the random mutations for the arriving key of the step, using the arriving records and the existing records.
        Specified by:
        planMutationsForKey in interface RandomPlanner
        Parameters:
        key - The row containing only the key fields and values.
        arrivingForKey - The arriving records of the key, from the DataFrame of the step.
        existingForKey - The existing records of the key, from the output of the step.
        Returns:
        The list of random mutations for the key to be applied to the output. The output will apply them in the same order as the list.
